1, 26. 1.. cruens] L. Licinius L. F. 1. N. Crassus, the celebrated orator mentioned 15108‚ 5 131, 11 5 47, 63, 111 5 67, Brut.5143. He was in all the offices but the tribuneship and censorship, colleague of Q. Mucius Scaevola (1 5 116). During his consulship he proposed a law, the lex Licinia Mucia (111547), to compel all who were not citizens to depart from Rome, the rigour of which law was one ot the causes of the Social War. He died me. 91, a few days after opposing in the Senate the consul L. Philippus, an enemy of the aristomacy. Crassus was fond of elegance and luxury: and his house upon the Palatium was one of the most beautiful at Rome, furnished with costly works of art. The pro« fuse display which attended his aedileship together with those of Scae· vola and Claudius is mentioned in the Verrine orations, 1v 59.
